<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="497" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,296,633]" box="[160,262,296,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,296,321]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,296,633]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">
This species is rather rarely found. After 
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun VM" box="[642,797,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" pagination="1 - 263" refId="ref6595" refString="Koltun VM. 1959. Kрiмнiрogovыi gubki сiviрныk i daльнivoсtocныk мoрiй СССР [Siliceous horny sponges of the northern and fareastern seas of the U. S. S. R.]. In: Pavlovsky EN, editor. Identifiers of the USSR fauna issued by the Zoological Institute of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR. Moscow - Leningrad: Nauka, Academy of Sciences of the USSR; Vol. 67, p. 1 - 263. Russian." type="journal article" year="1959">Koltun (1959)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<specimenCount box="[929,1102,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
collected near the Commander Islands, it was recorded only once, most likely wrongly, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sim CJ &amp; Kim HY &amp; Byeon HS" box="[160,341,401,425]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" pagination="123 - 144" refId="ref7411" refString="Sim CJ, Kim HY, Byeon HS. 1990. A systematic study on the marine sponges in Korea 8. Tetractinomorpha. Korean J Syst Zool. 6 (1): 123 - 144." type="journal article" year="1990">Sim et al. (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. Considering its spicules’ sizes and shapes, the sponge described by Sim from the East 
<collectingCountry box="[322,386,436,460]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">China</collectingCountry>
Sea is closer to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Koltun 1959)" baseAuthorityName="Koltun" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[575,906,436,460]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Axinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="blanca">
<emphasis box="[575,743,436,460]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">Axinella blanca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun VM" box="[758,897,436,460]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" pagination="1 - 263" refId="ref6595" refString="Koltun VM. 1959. Kрiмнiрogovыi gubki сiviрныk i daльнivoсtocныk мoрiй СССР [Siliceous horny sponges of the northern and fareastern seas of the U. S. S. R.]. In: Pavlovsky EN, editor. Identifiers of the USSR fauna issued by the Zoological Institute of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR. Moscow - Leningrad: Nauka, Academy of Sciences of the USSR; Vol. 67, p. 1 - 263. Russian." type="journal article" year="1959">Koltun 1959</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,296,633]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">
In total 
<specimenCount box="[280,455,470,494]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" type="generic">nine specimens</specimenCount>
found at depths of 
<quantity box="[683,809,470,494]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.94" metricValueMax="4.25" metricValueMin="1.63" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" unit="m" value="294.0" valueMax="425.0" valueMin="163.0">163–425 m</quantity>
were examined. The temperature and salinity in the bottom layer were 3.33–3.93°C and 35‰.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,296,633]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">In contrast to description of spicules given by Koltun, the skeleton of each of the examined specimens contained single strongyles – derivatives of styles, both thick and long.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
